Shop RHW is a Toronto-based studio with a focus on solid wood custom furniture hand crafted by Rundell Haynes-Wells. 
In addition to being a craftsman, he also offers custom design consultation and renderings.

Rundell combines years of experience problem solving, exploring, and innovating, and has been a maker of things all of his life.

profile:
Urban Woodcraft combines simplicity and durability of Mission-style furniture with the natural beauty of over 100-year-old robust wooden floorboards chosen by hand. Inspired by the simplicity of craftsman style furniture, each piece is handmade and naturally finished. This brings out the beauty, imperfections and character of our reclaimed planks, so no two pieces are exactly alike.
Our craftsmen hand pick only the finest natural solid wood planks to use in our creations. Absolutely no particle boards or veneers are used by any of our artisans when making our furniture. All of the wood used in our furniture is meticulously cut and finished by hand.
Each piece of Urban Woodcraft furniture is handmade by our expert artisans. Every piece is carefully wire-brushed by hand so that no two pieces are alike. Using only the finest reclaimed wood with natural and custom finishing options available for every piece of furniture we make, you can truly make our solid wood furniture your own.
Every piece of Urban Woodcraft furniture is finished by hand in our workshop by our team of devoted coloring specialists. Any custom finishing job that we do is quality ensured so that the grain and tone of the wood is never lost in the process.
